cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.HC, cs.IR, cs.SI

The paper utilizes deep learning techniques to classify mountainbike downhill trails based on sensor data. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC) as it aims to improve the user experience of mountainbike riders. Information Retrieval (cs.IR) may also be relevant as the paper deals with categorizing and organizing data. Finally, the paper involves signal processing (cs.SI) as it deals with accelerometer and gyroscope data.
